article.headline: N. Arizona 64, Utah Valley St. 63
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Matt Johnson scored 13 points and Zarko Comagic had 12 points and seven rebounds as Northern Arizona beat Utah Valley State 64-63 Saturday night to end a four-game losing streak. Cameron Jones added 12 points for the Lumberjacks (2-5). Ryan Toolson scored 18 of his game-high 25 points in the second half for Utah Valley State (4-3). Josh Olsen had 11 points for the Wolverines while Tyray Petty finished with 10. Northern Arizona led by as many as 12 points in the second half, but the Wolverines rallied to take a 57-55 lead on Toolson's 3-pointer with 2:43 left. The lead changed hands twice more before the Lumberjacks took a 60-59 lead with 1:38 remaining when Jones made a pair of free throws.
